Detailed Description

Internal implementation class for OBEX transport interfaces.

Warning;
This is an internal implementation class which must not be used outside APOXI OBEX at all.

It provides an implementation of the ObexAbstractPort interface suitable for server connections which is mainly a two-level nested state machine. The first level is implemented by ObexServerPort itself and represents the port state. The second level is used only temporarily to track the asynchronous execution of the following procedures:

  • Address resolution (updating of a service registry).

  • Detect when hardware becomes available and listen for incoming connection requests.

  • Detect when hardware becomes unavailable and release the associated resources.

The 2nd level state descriptions and there actions are inherited from the base class.
